main event: A large orange and white object was observed breaking up and trailing flame and debris from an elevation of 15,000 feet.
interesting points: The sighting was recorded on 10 November 1961 at 0603Z., The object was observed for about 5 seconds., The object was seen traveling at high speed and descending at an angle of 35 degrees from the horizon., The observation was evaluated as consistent with a bolide, or meteor., No identities of the object were determined on that date.
sighted object: large orange and white object breaking up
witness description: observed from an elevation of 15,000 feet.
